  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Randomized prospective study assessing suction drainage in total hip arthroplasty. Group
      without drainage, 50 hips, compared with group with suction drainage, 50 hips. Both groups
      will be asses clinically (ROM scale, VAS), laboratory and radiology (USG). In the actually
      literature there are no benefits using closed suction drainage after primary total hip
      arthroplasty.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
